### Area

admin/api

### Describe the bug

endpoint POST `/flows/{flowAlias}/executions/flow` to add a flow to an existing flow returns a header with the id of the generated flow, but this ID is not valid

### Version

main

### Regression

- [ ] The issue is a regression

### Expected behavior

The ID of the flow to be returned in the header of the request.

### Actual behavior

I'm not sure what is happening, but the ID that is returned is not used in when all the executions of the parent are called

### How to Reproduce?

we can use the keycloak-admin-client to show this:

```js
import KeycloakAdminClient from "@keycloak/keycloak-admin-client";

const client = new KeycloakAdminClient({
    baseUrl: "http://localhost:8080",
    realmName: "master",
  });

await client.auth({
        username: "admin",
        password: "admin",
        grantType: "password",
        clientId: "admin-cli",
      });

await client.authenticationManagement.createFlow({
        alias: "test",
        providerId: "basic-flow",
        description: "",
        topLevel: true,
        builtIn: false,
      });

const { id } = await client.authenticationManagement.addFlowToFlow({
            flow: "test",
            alias: "subFlow",
            description: "",
            provider: "registration-page-form",
            type: "basic-flow",
          });

console.log("flow", id);

const executions =
        await client.authenticationManagement.getExecutions({
          flow: "test",
        });

console.log("not the same", executions.find((e) => e.displayName === "subFlow")?.id)

```


